<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="482" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The President’s Secretary</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_ES1"><hi rend="italic">Early</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the President’s Administrative Assistant</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_DJW1"><hi rend="italic">Daniels</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Yalta</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-07">7 February 1945</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>From Mr. <persName corresp="#p_ES1">Early</persName> for Mr.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DJW1">Jonathan Daniels</persName>
                            </p>
                            <p>Pouch with letter, press conference transcript and so forth received.
                                Exceedingly regret troubles you are facing but can honestly assure
                                you our headaches are none the less severe. Situation here much too
                                involved to explain. All we can do is carry on best we can.
                                Regards.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>